area_name: Upper Cathedral Lakes, South Shore Buttress

content.description: The obvious, overhanging, right V crack. The block is well wedged but deserves circumspection. Tolerance of Belding's ground squirrel excrement is a must.
content.protection: Standard rack; extra #3 camlots might reduce gear fiddling
content.location: Near the left end of the west face is an obvious pair of crack that form a V; this is the right V crack.

content.description: Climb the cornerâ€™s intersecting cracks to a ledge with a small pine tree. Gain and then climb the right arching hand crack above.
content.location: Start at the right facing corner just up from the Templeton/Charlotte V.

content.description: Climb the crack that arches right through a wide section; up; pass a wide section; then thin hands to the top.
content.location: Start at the base of the curving crack; see photo

content.description: Climb the center crack in a short, north-facing cliff band above The Lemming Way. At the top, walk back 40 feet to the next cliff band for anchor crack and a trivial walk-off.
content.location: The left crack in a short, north-facing cliff band above The Lemming Way.

content.description: Start in the sandy corridor above Cody is Unimpressed; follow the crack up; soon a stellar hand-crack will arch out right to the top.
content.location: Either the 2nd pitch of Cody is Unimpressed or start this as its own climb from the sandy ledge at the top of Cody is Unimpressed.

content.description:
The obvious, steep, left V crack. The block is well wedged but deserves circumspection.

There is a short section of lower quality rock with few gear options between where the crack ends and the top.
content.protection: standard rack; extra hands/thin hands if you want extra
content.location: Near the left end of the west face is an obvious pair of cracks that form a V; this is the left V crack.
